activityList.description: Felt much better today than yesterday.
First run back from calf injury, then vertigo, then Covid. Seemed to go ok.
That felt better. Maybe the slightest pull after about 200 m but it was gone by the first quarter mile or so.
I think my left calf is on the mend.
Pretty rough even from the start. My left calf is still sore from May 27th. Though it has improved quite a bit. It was 84° when I started.
Calves are tired from hills on Monday. A 6:39 mile in there probably didn’t help.
GPS was way off. Distance and overall must be close. The last time I ran 6 miles was 2/19/2023.
Saw a small group of blue birds at the trail.
